INTRODUCTION : This paper will deal with the dat a processing educational needs and aspirations of Native Americans in general, an d the Navajo Tribe in particular . The curriculum described herein has bee n developed and implemented at Navaj o Community College, Tsaile (Navajo Nation) , Arizona over the past two years . ' The curriculum will be presented in terms o f specific courses and those technique s which have been used--some successfull y and others less so--in bridging the ga p between the traditionally rich and colorful Navajo tribe and this area of moder n technology .